### Phase 5: ScrollPane Consistency

#### 5.1 Settings Page Scrollable Content

The settings page returned by `SwissKitJSettingUi.build()` is placed inside a `ScrollPane` in `ContentArea.java` (line 255, via `pageScrollPane` which already has class `content-scroll` at line 190). So scroll styling for the settings page is already handled.

#### 5.2 Dialog ScrollBars

None of the three dialogs currently have `ScrollPane` wrappers. However, the `TableView` in the Address Book dialog (line 417) has 4 columns, and if content overflows, the default scrollbar will appear. Since `glass.css` already defines global scrollbar styles (lines 329-358), and the dialog scenes load `glass.css`, the scrollbars should pick up the glass styling automatically. No changes needed here.

However, if any dialog content needs explicit scroll panes, wrap in a `ScrollPane` with `content-scroll` class:

```java
ScrollPane sp = new ScrollPane(content);
sp.getStyleClass().add("content-scroll");
sp.setFitToWidth(true);
sp.setStyle("-fx-background-color: transparent;");
```

